  "root_text": {
    "dhp129:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp129:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp129:0.3": "Daṇḍavagga ",
    "dhp129:0.4": "Chabbaggiyabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp129:1": "Sabbe tasanti daṇḍassa, ",
    "dhp129:2": "sabbe bhāyanti maccuno; ",
    "dhp129:3": "Attānaṁ upamaṁ katvā, ",
    "dhp129:4": "na haneyya na ghātaye. ",
    "dhp130:0": "Chabbaggiyavatthu ",
    "dhp130:1": "Sabbe tasanti daṇḍassa, ",
    "dhp130:2": "sabbesaṁ jīvitaṁ piyaṁ; ",
    "dhp130:3": "Attānaṁ upamaṁ katvā, ",
    "dhp130:4": "na haneyya na ghātaye. ",
    "dhp131:0": "Sambahulakumārakavatthu ",
    "dhp131:1": "Sukhakāmāni bhūtāni, ",
    "dhp131:2": "yo daṇḍena vihiṁsati; ",
    "dhp131:3": "Attano sukhamesāno, ",
    "dhp131:4": "pecca so na labhate sukhaṁ. ",
    "dhp132:1": "Sukhakāmāni bhūtāni, ",
    "dhp132:2": "yo daṇḍena na hiṁsati; ",
    "dhp132:3": "Attano sukhamesāno, ",
    "dhp132:4": "pecca so labhate sukhaṁ. ",
    "dhp133:0": "Koṇḍadhānattheravatthu ",
    "dhp133:1": "Māvoca pharusaṁ kañci, ",
    "dhp133:2": "vuttā paṭivadeyyu taṁ; ",
    "dhp133:3": "Dukkhā hi sārambhakathā, ",
    "dhp133:4": "paṭidaṇḍā phuseyyu taṁ. ",
    "dhp134:1": "Sace neresi attānaṁ, ",
    "dhp134:2": "kaṁso upahato yathā; ",
    "dhp134:3": "Esa pattosi nibbānaṁ, ",
    "dhp134:4": "sārambho te na vijjati. ",
    "dhp135:0": "Uposathikaitthīnaṁvatthu ",
    "dhp135:1": "Yathā daṇḍena gopālo, ",
    "dhp135:2": "gāvo pājeti gocaraṁ; ",
    "dhp135:3": "Evaṁ jarā ca maccu ca, ",
    "dhp135:4": "āyuṁ pājenti pāṇinaṁ. ",
    "dhp136:0": "Ajagarapetavatthu ",
    "dhp136:1": "Atha pāpāni kammāni, ",
    "dhp136:2": "karaṁ bālo na bujjhati; ",
    "dhp136:3": "Sehi kammehi dummedho, ",
    "dhp136:4": "aggidaḍḍhova tappati. ",
    "dhp137:0": "Mahāmoggallānattheravatthu ",
    "dhp137:1": "Yo daṇḍena adaṇḍesu, ",
    "dhp137:2": "appaduṭṭhesu dussati; ",
    "dhp137:3": "Dasannamaññataraṁ ṭhānaṁ, ",
    "dhp137:4": "khippameva nigacchati. ",
    "dhp138:1": "Vedanaṁ pharusaṁ jāniṁ, ",
    "dhp138:2": "sarīrassa va bhedanaṁ; ",
    "dhp138:3": "Garukaṁ vāpi ābādhaṁ, ",
    "dhp138:4": "cittakkhepaṁ va pāpuṇe. ",
    "dhp139:1": "Rājato vā upasaggaṁ, ",
    "dhp139:2": "Abbhakkhānaṁ va dāruṇaṁ; ",
    "dhp139:3": "Parikkhayaṁ va ñātīnaṁ, ",
    "dhp139:4": "Bhogānaṁ va pabhaṅguraṁ. ",
    "dhp140:1": "Atha vāssa agārāni, ",
    "dhp140:2": "aggi ḍahati pāvako; ",
    "dhp140:3": "Kāyassa bhedā duppañño, ",
    "dhp140:4": "nirayaṁ sopapajjati. ",
    "dhp141:0": "Bahubhaṇḍikabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp141:1": "Na naggacariyā na jaṭā na paṅkā, ",
    "dhp141:2": "Nānāsakā thaṇḍilasāyikā vā; ",
    "dhp141:3": "Rajojallaṁ ukkuṭikappadhānaṁ, ",
    "dhp141:4": "Sodhenti maccaṁ avitiṇṇakaṅkhaṁ. ",
    "dhp142:0": "Santatimahāmattavatthu ",
    "dhp142:1": "Alaṅkato cepi samaṁ careyya, ",
    "dhp142:2": "Santo danto niyato brahmacārī; ",
    "dhp142:3": "Sabbesu bhūtesu nidhāya daṇḍaṁ, ",
    "dhp142:4": "So brāhmaṇo so samaṇo sa bhikkhu. ",
    "dhp143:0": "Pilotikatissattheravatthu ",
    "dhp143:1": "Hirīnisedho puriso, ",
    "dhp143:2": "koci lokasmi vijjati; ",
    "dhp143:3": "Yo niddaṁ apabodheti, ",
    "dhp143:4": "asso bhadro kasāmiva. ",
    "dhp144:1": "Asso yathā bhadro kasāniviṭṭho, ",
    "dhp144:2": "Ātāpino saṁvegino bhavātha; ",
    "dhp144:3": "Saddhāya sīlena ca vīriyena ca, ",
    "dhp144:4": "Samādhinā dhammavinicchayena ca; ",
    "dhp144:5": "Sampannavijjācaraṇā patissatā, ",
    "dhp144:6": "Jahissatha dukkhamidaṁ anappakaṁ. ",
    "dhp145:0": "Sukhasāmaṇeravatthu ",
    "dhp145:1": "Udakañhi nayanti nettikā, ",
    "dhp145:2": "Usukārā namayanti tejanaṁ; ",
    "dhp145:3": "Dāruṁ namayanti tacchakā, ",
    "dhp145:4": "Attānaṁ damayanti subbatā. ",
    "dhp145:5": "Daṇḍavaggo dasamo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp129:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp129:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 129–145 ",
    "dhp129:0.3": "10. The Rod ",
    "dhp129:0.4": "",
    "dhp129:1": "All tremble at the rod, ",
    "dhp129:2": "all fear death. ",
    "dhp129:3": "Treating others like oneself, ",
    "dhp129:4": "neither kill nor incite to kill. ",
    "dhp130:1": "All tremble at the rod, ",
    "dhp130:2": "all love life. ",
    "dhp130:3": "Treating others like oneself, ",
    "dhp130:4": "neither kill nor incite to kill. ",
    "dhp131:1": "Creatures love happiness, ",
    "dhp131:2": "so if you harm them with a stick ",
    "dhp131:3": "in search of your own happiness, ",
    "dhp131:4": "after death you won’t find happiness. ",
    "dhp132:1": "Creatures love happiness, ",
    "dhp132:2": "so if you don’t harm them with a stick ",
    "dhp132:3": "in search of your own happiness, ",
    "dhp132:4": "after death you will find happiness. ",
    "dhp133:1": "Don’t speak harshly, ",
    "dhp133:2": "they may speak harshly back. ",
    "dhp133:3": "For aggressive speech is painful, ",
    "dhp133:4": "and the rod may spring back on you. ",
    "dhp134:1": "If you still yourself ",
    "dhp134:2": "like a broken gong, ",
    "dhp134:3": "you reach extinguishment ",
    "dhp134:4": "and know no conflict. ",
    "dhp135:1": "As a cowherd drives the cows ",
    "dhp135:2": "to pasture with the rod, ",
    "dhp135:3": "so too old age and death ",
    "dhp135:4": "drive life from living beings. ",
    "dhp136:1": "The fool does not understand ",
    "dhp136:2": "the evil that they do. ",
    "dhp136:3": "But because of those deeds, that simpleton ",
    "dhp136:4": "is tormented as if burnt by fire. ",
    "dhp137:1": "One who violently attacks ",
    "dhp137:2": "the peaceful and the innocent ",
    "dhp137:3": "swiftly falls ",
    "dhp137:4": "to one of ten bad states: ",
    "dhp138:1": "harsh pain; loss; ",
    "dhp138:2": "the breakup of the body; ",
    "dhp138:3": "serious illness; ",
    "dhp138:4": "mental distress; ",
    "dhp139:1": "hazards from rulers; ",
    "dhp139:2": "vicious slander; ",
    "dhp139:3": "loss of kin; ",
    "dhp139:4": "destruction of wealth; ",
    "dhp140:1": "or else their home ",
    "dhp140:2": "is consumed by fire. ",
    "dhp140:3": "When their body breaks up, that witless person ",
    "dhp140:4": "is reborn in hell. ",
    "dhp141:1": "Not nudity, nor matted hair, nor mud, ",
    "dhp141:2": "nor fasting, nor lying on bare ground, ",
    "dhp141:3": "nor wearing dust and dirt, or squatting on the heels, ",
    "dhp141:4": "will cleanse a mortal not free of doubt. ",
    "dhp142:1": "Dressed up they may be, but if they live well—",
    "dhp142:2": "peaceful, tamed, committed to the spiritual path, ",
    "dhp142:3": "having laid aside violence towards all creatures—",
    "dhp142:4": "they are a brahmin, an ascetic, a mendicant. ",
    "dhp143:1": "Can a person constrained by conscience ",
    "dhp143:2": "be found in the world? ",
    "dhp143:3": "Who shies away from blame, ",
    "dhp143:4": "like a fine horse from the whip? ",
    "dhp144:1": "Like a fine horse under the whip, ",
    "dhp144:2": "be keen and full of urgency. ",
    "dhp144:3": "With faith, ethics, and energy, ",
    "dhp144:4": "immersion, and investigation of principles, ",
    "dhp144:5": "accomplished in knowledge and conduct, mindful, ",
    "dhp144:6": "give up this vast suffering. ",
    "dhp145:1": "While irrigators guide water, ",
    "dhp145:2": "fletchers shape arrows, ",
    "dhp145:3": "and carpenters carve timber—",
    "dhp145:4": "those true to their vows tame themselves. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "dhp133:2": "paṭivadeyyu taṁ → paṭivadeyyuṁ taṁ (mr) ",
    "dhp133:4": "paṭidaṇḍā phuseyyu taṁ → phuseyyuṁ taṁ (mr) ",
    "dhp138:2": "sarīrassa va bhedanaṁ → sarīrassa pabhedanaṁ (cck) ",
    "dhp138:4": "cittakkhepaṁ va → cittakkhepañca (pts1ed, pts2ed, csp1ed) ",
    "dhp139:1": "upasaggaṁ → upassaggaṁ (bj, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp139:2": "Abbhakkhānaṁ va → abbhakkhānañca (csp1ed) ",
    "dhp139:3": "Parikkhayaṁ va → parikkhayañca (csp1ed) ",
    "dhp139:4": "Bhogānaṁ va → bhogānañca (csp1ed) | pabhaṅguraṁ → pabhaṅguṇaṁ (sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed); pabhaṅgunaṁ (mr) ",
    "dhp140:2": "ḍahati → ḍayhati (mr) ",
    "dhp140:4": "sopapajjati → so upapajjati (bj, sya-all, pts1ed) ",
    "dhp143:3": "niddaṁ → nindaṁ (bj, pts1ed, pts2ed sn1.18:1 [18. Hirīsutta]) | apabodheti → apabodhati (bj sn1.18:1 [18. Hirīsutta]); appabodheti (cck); appabodhati (pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp144:6": "Jahissatha → pahassatha (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) "
  },
